<h2>What is Quicksort ?</h2>
<p>Quicksort is a community-operated link farm grouped by topics.</p>

<p>
  The main goal is to organize the content on the internet, in order to make it easier to find what you want.
  Think of it as a 2-step google search:
  instead of searching directly what you want on google, you first find the quicksort page, then find what you want in this page.
</p>

<div class="well">
  <span>
    For example, say you want to find a good service for downloading a youtube video. With google, you will find sites whose owners know how to do seo best. With quicksort,
    you will find user submitted results based on how useful the link/service actually is (thanks to the upvote/downvote
    mechanism).
  </span>
</div>

<b>Old way</b>
<ul>
  <li>Search "download youtube video" on google</li>
  <li>Try first link. Not what you want</li>
  <li>Try second link. Kind of what do want, but not really</li>
  <li>Try third link. What you want. Cool, but at the very end you have to pay</li>
  <li>Try fourth link. Website with adds everywhere</li>
  <li>(╯°□°）╯︵ ┻━┻)</li>
  <li>Give up</li>
  <li>Ask for a friend</li>
  <li>Friend tells you about a service that was on 5th page. Exactly what you want. Why was this not the first result?
  </li>
</ul>
<b>Quicksort way&trade;</b>

<ul>
  <li>Search "download youtube video inurl:quicksort" on google</li>
  <li>Click top quicksort link</li>
  <li>Select the service/link that best corresponds to what you want among the top ones</li>
  <li>Yes, quicksort is awesome. You can put the table back</li>
  <li>┬──┬ ノ( ゜-゜ノ)</li>
</ul>

