<h2>Show me more examples</h2>
<p class="note" style="margin-bottom: 0;padding-bottom: 0">
  Good example are usually topics that you can easily answer with a list of links.
</p>
<h3>Good topic examples</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Easy way to download a youtube video</li>
  <li>Queen songs</li>
  <li>Web frameworks in PHP</li>
  <li>Trending social apps</li>
  <li>Free resources to learn music online</li>
</ul>
<h3>Bad topic examples</h3>
<ul>
  <li>How to sort an array of integers in ruby (To specific. Belongs on stackoverflow)</li>
  <li>How to better sleep at night (Too broad. Belongs on quora)</li>
  <li>Recent advances in technology (Too broad. Belongs on reddit /r/technology)</li>
</ul>

<h2>This is amazing, how do I get started ?</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    Next time you look for something specific on the internet, create a topic. And as you find good links for it,
    add them to your own topic (it could be right away or later). You people will thank you by upvoting your
    topic and links, and you might also have people adding links you didn't know about.
  </li>
  <li>
    Whenever you find a very good piece of content, bookmark it in a folder called "List of useful". When this
    bookmark gets too big, submit all the links to quicksort on the page "List of usefull". Then you organize them
    into topics, (or let other people do that if you don't have time)
  </li>
  <li>
    Create an account
  </li>
  <li>
    Tell your friends
  </li>

</ul>

